Cape Town – The Anti-Gang Unit has arrested a gunman after he allegedly shot a disabled man who was a witness in a court case. Cops say Anti-Gang Unit members were called to Begonia Street in Uitsig, Ravensmead, on Tuesday afternoon, where they found the body of the 23-year-old man. He has only one leg. It is believed the gunman, who had been on foot, shot the man, only identified as Heinwin, while he sat behind security gates. At the scene, community members informed the Daily Voice that the man was expected to testify in court but would not reveal further details about the case. Police spokesperson Lieutenant-Colonel Andre Traut confirmed the arrest. “The circumstances surrounding the death of a 23-year-old man are being investigated after he was shot and killed in Begonia Street, Uitsig, Ravensmead, on Tuesday," Traut said. “Members of the Anti-Gang Unit responded to the incident and arrested the suspect. Once charged, he is due to make a court appearance for murder.”